overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification and an existing codebase. The agent
  performed a comprehensive review, identifying several gaps, including a
  missing tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and insufficient sleep
  syndrome detection. Following a prioritized plan, the agent implemented these
  features. This involved updating the data types and validation schemas,
  modifying the questionnaire's UI to include the severity slider and associated
  safety warnings, and enhancing the report generation logic in both the web and
  PDF versions to detect and provide tailored recommendations for COMISA and
  insufficient sleep syndrome. The agent ensured that all changes were
  consistently applied across the application's components.
